# Coriolis — Bill of Materials

Hardware parts list for the Wind Lab long-range wind-sensing system.

**System shape**

- **N sensor nodes** — each = one T-Beam + one wind meter + the daughterboard, deployed downrange.
- **1 base station / receiver** — a T-Beam that coordinates the nodes over LoRa, runs the ballistic solver, and serves the phone dashboard over its own WiFi AP. No wind meter of its own. The daughterboard is not required for the base station, but is recommended. If the daughterboard is not used, the user will have to source their own enclosure.

Quantities are **per node** unless marked *(base)* or *(shared)*. Replace **N** with your node count; you buy **N + 1** T-Beams total. Prices are rough USD for planning only — **verify current pricing/availability at purchase.**

> Everything below is matched to what the current firmware actually expects (chip identities, I²C addresses, radio, PMU). Substituting a part usually means a small firmware change — see [Notes & gotchas](#notes--gotchas).

