## 2. Wind meters — pick one type per node (firmware auto-detects at boot)

| Option | Item | Qty | Details | Approx. USD |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **A — SparkFun** | Weather Meter Parts | 0–N | Cup anemometer (1.492 mph/Hz) + 8-position resistor wind vane mast/clamps, RJ11 cables. Cheapest; direction resolves to ~8 points (~13° steps). | ~$60 |
| **B — Inspeed** | Vortex Wind Speed Sensor (2.5 mph/Hz; reed or WS2 Hall, sensor-only) | 0–N | Rugged anemometer, 5–125 mph, 1 pulse/rev. | ~$70–100 |
| **B — Inspeed** | e-Vane II (EV2) ratiometric Hall vane | 0–N | Continuous (high-res) direction, 5–95% Vcc analog out, near-zero deadband. Pairs with the Vortex. | ~$90–110 |

Firmware detects SparkFun vs. Inspeed automatically (2 LED blinks = SparkFun, 3 = Inspeed) — no jumper, no per-node `#define`. SparkFun = one kit per node; Inspeed = Vortex + e-Vane II per node.

Vendors: SparkFun (`sparkfun.com/weather-meter-kit.html`), Inspeed (`store.inspeed.com`).

