## 3. Node sensor daughterboard — custom PCB, 1 per node

Not a commercial board — this is the small carrier that holds the wind-sensor MCU + barometer and plugs onto the T-Beam's I²C bus (SDA/SCL/3V3/GND). Fab it from the repo's board files; it is populated with:

| Component | Qty/board | Details | Approx. USD |
|---|---|---|---|
| **ATtiny85** (DIP-8 or SOIC-8) | 1 | Wind-sensor MCU, 3.3 V, 8 MHz internal, I²C addr `0x42`. Reads vane on PB3/ADC3, anemometer pulse on PB4, talks I²C to the T-Beam (PB0=SDA, PB2=SCL), boot LED on PB1. | ~$1–2 |
| **BMP180 barometer/temp module** (GY-68) | 1 | I²C baro+temp (addr `0x77`), via `Adafruit_BMP085` library. Legacy part (see gotchas). | ~$3–6 |
| **Wind-meter connector** | 1 | RJ11 6P jack for the SparkFun cable, or a 3-pos screw terminal for Inspeed's bare leads. | ~$1 |
| Passives & I/O | — | I²C pull-ups 4.7 kΩ ×2, 0.1 µF decoupling, boot LED + ~330 Ω, vane input resistor, and a header to the T-Beam. Exact values/quantities come from the board schematic. | ~$1 |
| **PCB fabrication** | 1 | From repo Gerbers. | ~$Unknown |

