## Notes & gotchas

- **Radio must match firmware.** The code uses RadioLib on an SX1276 at 915 MHz. SX1262 / ESP32-S3 "Supreme"/"1W" boards require a radio-driver change — pick the classic SX1276 915 MHz T-Beam.
- **PMU either revision is fine.** AXP2101 (v1.2, current) and AXP192 (v1.1, older) are both auto-detected via XPowersLib.
- **BMP180 is end-of-life.** Modules are still around; if you can't source one, BMP280/BME280 is a small library swap (`Adafruit_BMP085` → `Adafruit_BMP280`/`BME280`) — that's a firmware edit, so flag it before substituting.
- **ATtiny85 at 3.3 V.** Program at 8 MHz internal so its I²C levels match the T-Beam. Address is fixed at `0x42`.
- **Direction resolution differs by meter.** SparkFun ≈ 8 points (~13° quantization); Inspeed e-Vane II is continuous. The firmware's per-meter quality thresholds already account for this — you can mix meter types across nodes.
- **OLED variant.** Buy the T-Beam with the OLED (soldered, or solder the included one) — the node and receiver both use it.

